One that comes to mind is Genghis Khan.  This game is set in the 13th century and the setting is pretty much the entire northern hemisphere (minus North America).<br /><br />The music for Japan, track 4.  It sounds extremely unrelenting, but I think it's cool.  If you use Japan when learning to play this game, you may hear this song for hours on end.<br /><br />track 8 is really weird.  It has some tempo changes that are really unsettling, I don't know if it sounds cool but it is unique.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Feb 16, 2010 3:00 pm</p><hr />
