<title type="html"><![CDATA[Extremely simple music]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6056&amp;p=56678#p56678"><![CDATA[
I figured that some video games have music tunes which are ridiculously simple / weird, that normally would sound stupid for having only 1 voice and/or repeating after a very short while, but that for an obscure reason sounds cool.<br /><br />Some examples I can think of :<br />Of course <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f0fZl5OjOi0&amp;feature=related" class="postlink">this song</a> from SMB it only has ONE voice (played on 2 channels) and repeats after 12 secs but it does sound pretty good<br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vWJEpr8U_aY&amp;feature=related" class="postlink">This song</a> from Wario Land is really mysterious<br /><br />Another one, slightly more advanced but still fairly simple that I REALLY like is the Gun Smoke menu music. I didn't find it on Youtube but you just have to play Gun Smoke and press select. It's dumb and repeats quickly, yet it sets an AWESOME mod for such a simple song.<br /><br />Anyone have other example of incredibly simple songs that sounds cool ? And please don't mention that MM2 get weapon songs, yes i know everyone like it but I don't it get on my nerves.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Feb 16, 2010 12:06 pm</p><hr />
